I remember just about everything about that drive because for the first time in my life I was seeing the world clearly.

00:38:22.912 --> 00:38:24.694
I love to go to basketball games with my dad.

00:38:25.975 --> 00:38:28.758
We actually had decent seats, but it didn't matter where I was sitting because I was blind.

00:38:28.998 --> 00:38:38.507
But I had learned to compensate for it and I could kind of tell, the blurry numbers or blurry heads or shapes or tall, I could tell which players were which, but I had to work pretty hard on it.

00:38:38.627 --> 00:38:40.169
I had no idea that I was working hard.

00:38:40.609 --> 00:38:41.129
I just had to work.

00:38:41.230 --> 00:38:46.034
I remember going to the first game where I put my glasses on and I actually could see the players.

00:38:46.306 --> 00:38:47.868
in front of me on the basketball court.

00:38:48.289 --> 00:38:51.574
I remember what it was like to have my vision clear for the first time.

00:38:51.954 --> 00:38:57.122
Giving into sexual sin, I think, is like having the glasses and throwing them away.

00:39:00.347 --> 00:39:04.613
It's forfeiting the opportunity to see and see clearly.

00:39:05.154 --> 00:39:07.898
We're not looking at trees or basketball players or big lots.

00:39:08.699 --> 00:39:10.762
We're looking at God.

00:39:10.782 --> 00:39:14.267
And so do whatever clears your eyes to see and enjoy Jesus.

00:39:14.448 --> 00:39:16.050
Avoid whatever blurs your eyes.

00:39:16.738 --> 00:39:19.477
and divide your heart against him.

00:39:19.497 --> 00:39:21.874
Blessed are the pure in heart for they shall see God.
